column35:
Company Overview



Hamilton Company is a worldwide leader in the design and manufacture of manual, semi-automated and robotic products for precision fluid measuring. We specialize in the development, manufacturing and customization of precision measurement devices, automated liquid handling stations, and sample management systems. For more than 60 years, Hamilton has been satisfying customer needs by combining quality materials with skilled workmanship, ensuring the highest level of performance of every precision fluid measuring device we manufacture.



Responsibilities



Hamilton Robotics is seeking a Service Technician to join our Robotics team, supporting, repairing, and maintaining robotic instrumentation. As a Service Technician with Hamilton Company you will be tasked with providing high quality repairs of electromechanical systems for customers as well as for internal company use.



Other Responsibilities:
column43: Troubleshoot and repair Hamilton equipment.
column46: Perform preventative maintenance.
column48: Report problems and perform root cause analysis on instrument failures.
column64: Fill out paperwork and reports related to any repair work.
column69: Manage work station inventory for commonly used repair parts.
column71: Other duties as assigned.
column73: A high desire for quality.
column76: Demonstrated experience working in production as well as an office setting.
column79: Ability and willingness to work in a safety conscious manner necessary due to potential hazardous chemicals and biologicals.
column82: Ability to learn new robotic operating systems.
column84: Excellent written and verbal communication and collaboration skills.
column89: An Associate's Degree in Engineering Technology or comparable is preferred .
column92: Minimum of 2 years Technician experience, preferably in the biotech / life science field.
column95: Ability to lift, carry, push, pull or otherwise move approximately 60 lbs.
column97: Diverse portfolio of exciting and innovative design projects
column100: Tremendous opportunities for professional growth
column103: Commitment to sustainable design
column105: Competitive Compensation
column107: Excellent Benefit Package includes medical, dental, vision insurance, paid vacation time, paid sick time, disability insurance, 401k, tuition reimbursement and much more
column111: Solid Stable Company

column34:
Responsible for performing a variety of duties in relation to imaging patients and ensuring smooth operations of the Diagnostic Imaging and Interventional Radiology departments while providing appropriate levels of patient care and customer service.



Responsibilities



Safety



Manages processes effectively in regard to employee/patient



Record Keeping



Maintains all required records, reports, statistics, logs, files and other documents as required.



Process Improvement



Promotes a culture of process improvement by participating in unit/department based programs that supports the systems process improvement goals.

Actively participates on system-wide or hospital-based teams as



Role Specific Responsibilities



Performs diagnostic radiographic exams.

Utilizes PACS and EMR systems

Performs interventional procedures per protocol and established procedures.

Maintains appropriate IV and Contrast Competency

Follows established protocols and procedures for proper patient position, exposure control, and radiation protection.

Communicates clearly and effectively with all involved in the patient care process.

Cleans and inspects departmental equipment

Cleans and stocks Imaging rooms.



Qualifications



Education



Associate degree



Licenses and Certification



ARRT Certification in Radiology

IEMA

BLS



Experience and Skills



Technical experience: 3 years preferred



#PIQImage

PandoLogic. , Location: Marion, IL - 62959

column35:
The Behavioral Health Consultant provides primary care-based behavioral health services to clients with complex or chronic needs depending on assigned program as determined in the treatment or care plan of the client. Counseling or therapeutic services are provided as part of a team, with primary care-based services being integrated into the care plan directed by the primary care provider. We offer this position at either PsyD/PhD clinical psychologist, or independently licensed Master s-level mental health therapist.



What We Offer
column43: Clinical Psychologist:
column46: $10,000 hiring bonus paid in first paycheck.
column48: Salary $120,000.
column64: Master s-level independently licensed therapist:
column69: $5,000 hiring bonus in first paycheck, $2,000 bonus at 12 months.
column71: Salary $100,000.
column73: 100% employer-paid health insurance for employees including Medical, Dental, Vision, Rx, 24/7 telemedicine; profit sharing, 403(b) retirement plan, generous paid time off, paid holidays, continuing education, and more.
column76: Responds to requests from primary care providers to address behavioral health needs of medical clinic patients to maintain a warm hand-off for most patient encounters.
column79: Provides brief intervention for presenting problems and triage for on-going treatment services as needed.
column82: Completes encounters and associated documentation, including coding and billing.
column84: Presents case studies and reports to funding sources or as requested by outside organizations.
column89: Measures change and adjusts treatment as needed, using appropriate screening tools.
column92: Provides cognitive behavioral therapy to individuals, families, groups or communities as assigned. Integrates cognitive behavioral interventions in multiple settings.
column95: Enters documentation into the electronic medical record (EMR).
column97: Responds to crisis situations, assessing urgency of patient s needs, provides care, and obtains appropriate services as needed.
column100: Assists patient and family in obtaining additional services and other resources as needed. Documents all referrals made to other resources.
column103: As assigned, participates in various community meetings and serves as a liaison to numerous community agencies and organizations, including school districts, hospitals, law enforcement, Division of Children and Family Services (DCFS) staff, and tribal authorities.
column105: Presents mental health/behavioral health findings and recommendations in verbal or written format to appropriate professionals either upon request or as part of a regular case presentation for peer review or clinical meeting.
column107: Leads staff training sessions on new therapeutic techniques and practices. Provides training and education on clinical topics to team members, staff and the community, as needed.
column111: Performs clinical responsibilities in alignment with The Joint Commission (TJC), Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA), and YVFWC requirements.
column114: Education: Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D.) or Doctor of Psychology (Psy.D.) in Clinical Psychology.
column117: Experience Preferred: One year's clinical experience working within a multidisciplinary team in primary care or other medical settings providing diagnostic and psychological assessments, for primary care-based positions. One year's clinical experience working with children, adolescents and families for specialty behavioral health settings.
column120: Licenses/Registration: Licensed Psychologist within the state of practice. First Aid/Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) Certification obtained within 45 days of employment.
column122: Education: Master s Degree in Social Work, Psychology, Counseling or related field.
column125: Experience: Two years experience postgraduate/master s experience in the direct treatment of persons with mental illness or emotional disturbance; such experience must have been gained under the supervision of a mental health professional.
column129: Licenses/Certificates/Registration: One of the following licenses is required for this position (must apply for within one week of hire if the license is not current):
column132: Oregon State Board of Licensed Social Workers
column143: Basic Life Support (BLS) Certification obtained within 45 days of hire.
column147:
About YVFWC



We serve more than 197,000 patients across 28 medical clinics, 15 dental clinics, 11 pharmacies, and 49 program sites in two states. We are Level 3 Certified as a Patient-Centered Medical Home (PCMH). With integrated services including medical, dental, pharmacy, orthodontia, primary care nutritional counseling, autism screening, and primary care behavioral health, YVFWC s patient-centered model of care offers patients the full spectrum of care and shelter assistance, energy assistance, weatherization, HIV and AIDS counseling and testing, home visits, and four mobile medical/dental clinics.



Working at YVFWC



Working in our organization means being the passionate champion for those who have no voice. It means having the opportunity to work with underserved populations and with peers committed to the same work.



At Farm Workers Clinic

column35:
Overview:

POSITION SUMMARY

The Fiber Splicer is experienced in installing, prepping, and splicing Fiber Optic Cabling in ISP and OSP environments.  They must also be able to read and interpret construction diagrams and blueprints.

 

$5,000 Sign On Bonus Available for all new hires! 

 

ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS
column43: Install, prep and splice Fiber Optic Cabling in ISP and OSP environments
column46: Splice fiber optic cables including both loose tube and ribbon cables
column48: Operate technical equipment, including but not limited to a laptop computer, OTDR and fusion splicing equipment for single and ribbon fiber
column64: Read and interpret existing fiber records, on maps or in the field
column69: Complete daily production reports to document work performed; track and communicate daily production and materials
column71: Construct proper splice case, including but not limited to grounding, bonding, isolation, slack storage, and sealing.
column73: Able to troubleshoot and resolve problems discovered on the job
column76: Follow design engineer instructions
column79: Recognize and repair route issues
column82: Must wear personal protective equipment (PPE) while working including but not limited to hard hat, DOT compliant reflective shirts and vests, work boots, and safety goggles
column84: Maintain and promote a safe working environment for yourself and the other members of your team
column89: Flexibility to travel as needed for assigned projects
column92: Other duties as assigned
column95: Regularly lift and/or move up to 100lbs
column97: Ability to work in remote or congested traffic areas
column100: Willingness to work outdoors in every type of weather
column103: Ability to work alone with minimal supervision
column105: Ability to work safely
column107: The ability and experience in operating various hand tools, and basic computer equipment
column111: Possess a valid driver's license with a good driving record
column114: Splicing experience
column117: Must be able to pass a pre-employment drug test
column130:

The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by people assigned to this classification. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required of personnel so classified. All personnel may be required to perform duties outside of their normal responsibilities from time to time, as needed.

column35:
Children's Activities Associate at Kids Quest - TREASURE ISLAND RESORT & CASINO

Kids Quest Company Description:

Kids Quest is the largest hourly childcare provider and entertainment facility, offering play, games, and birthday parties at our partner resorts.

Our team is looking for a Children's Activities Associate to help join and lead our team!

Benefits and Perks of a Children's Activities Associate:
column43: Get Paid to Play - Earn tips on top of your hourly wage rate!
column46: Paid Trainings - Learn and gain leadership skills that you can use inside and outside of work!
column48: Health & Wellness Benefits - taking care of you and your family! For full time employees we offer health, vision and dental care plans. For all employees we have fun wellness programs like walking competitions with prizes, free employee assistance programs for overall wellness
column64: Plan for Your Future - we offer 401(k) for all employees including 401(k) company matching
column69: Discounts on Personal Child Care - receive half (50%) off the hourly child care rate for children between the ages of 30 months to 12 years of age! Have your kids play while you work and have fun!
column71: Quarterly Incentive Team Challenges - by being a part of our management team, you can help create fun team challenges to incentivize center growth and productivity.
column73: Monthly Team Rallies - Bring your pep and your cheer! Each month we celebrate our successes as a team and create new goals to help grow the business!
column76: Career Advancement Opportunities - we love to promote from within! We have a robust training program that will help you excel to the next level within our company! We strive to ensure our people have first opportunities when new center openings or positions are made available company-wide!
column79: Free Slushies and Half Off Food - Getting thirsty on job! No problem! Enjoy free slushies and free fountain drinks while working! Also, if you forget your lunch, help yourself to any of our food items for half (50%) off!!
column81: Job Summary of a Children s Activities Associate :
column82: You are a genuine, caring and responsible individual who can enthusiastically play and engage with children between the ages of 6 weeks through 12 years old. You have the skills to supervise our young guests responsibly and respectfully by bringing energy, excitement and fun to their lives while entrusted to our care.
column83: Qualification and Must-Have Skills of a Children s Activities Associate:
column84: Be passionate about play and children, enjoy meeting new people
column89: Must be able to complete and pass required background screening (which may include a drug test)
column92: Ability to work a variety of shifts, this includes evenings, weekends, and holidays
column95: A high school diploma, G.E.D. or equivalent (required)
column97: Experience in child care, day care, nannying, babysitting, and even coaching children s sports is a plus!
column100: Military veterans or reservists are encouraged to apply!
column103: Must be 18 years of age or older and can work in a casino/gaming environment
column105: Ability to handle changing priorities and use good judgment in stressful situations
column107: Basic computer proficiency and cash handling experience (preferred)
column109: Children s Activities Associate Core Job Duties:
column111: Report to your center management team while on duty.
column114: Come to work each day on-time, motivated and with a positive attitude.
column117: Understand and follow cash control processes and procedures.
column120: Maintain the Kids Quest dress code standards while on duty.
column122: Attend all scheduled meetings, workshops and required training programs
column125: Abide by all Kids Quest policies
column129: Embrace a fast-paced work and high-traffic play environment.
column134:
Apply now! Don't let this opportunity to have a fun, rewarding job pass you by!

Benefits:
column149:
• Weekend availability

    • COVID-19 considerations:

    All employees must pass a wellness screening prior to reporting to work. Masks are not required but optional upon employee discretion.

    Ability to commute/relocate:

  • Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)

    • Application Question(s):

  • Are you available to work week days until 11pm and weekends as late as 1am? Please let us know your availability.

    • Education:

  • High school or equivalent (Required)

    • Experience:

  • Childcare: 1 year (Preferred)

    • Work Location: In person

    #TREASUREKQ

column34:
Overview:

Duration: Full-Time

Location: Traveling up to 75% of the time

Pay Rate: Unit Base Pay

 

Applicants must be authorized to work in the United States.

 SQUAN is seeking dedicated field engineers to join our team. As a field engineer, you will play a crucial role in gathering OSP field information, ensuring accuracy, and contributing to the success of our nationwide telecom projects. We are looking for candidates within the central or eastern time zone and are willing to travel up to 75% of the time. Responsibilities:* Utilize company-provided equipment to collect and transmit field data.* Work safely in diverse environments* Gather information vital for telecom design including pole attachments, construction path measurements, buried facilities, right-of-way and roadway dimensions, and inventory of cabinets and buildings. Your detailed notes will aid in the design and construction processes.* Communicate obstacles and challenges promptly to facilitate quick problem-solving. Requirements:* Willingness to travel, covering up to 75% of the year, exploring various locations to gather essential field data.

* Possess and maintain reliable transportation for all travel.* Have the ability to read and interpret online and printed maps* Exhibit effective communication skills, both verbal and written.* Maintain a professional appearance and strong work ethic even while working without direct supervision.* Proficiency in AutoCAD is preferred, but not required. Benefits:* A culture that values opportunity for growth, development, and internal promotion* Medial, Dental, and Vision benefit programs* Life Insurance* Paid Holidays, Vacation, and Sick Time* 401K with Company MatchEmployee Referral Program ABOUT SQUANWe are a fast-growing telecommunications engineering and construction company that is working with America’s telecom and internet providers to build a nationwide network offering every American home and business access to very high-speed, fiber optic internet connections. The hard-working men and women in our engineering division design networks to guarantee the country’s high-speed internet and 5G cellular service is the best in the world. We have 400 employees today, but we’ll need to double that number by 2024. We are only looking for people who are ambitious and self-motivated.

column32: A propos de l'entreprise :Nous recherchons un(e) chirurgien-dentiste motivé(e)s pour nous rejoindre. Vousêtes à la recherche d'un nouveau challenge sur Alfortville Jeune thésé(e) ouexpérimenté(e), nous avons actuellement un poste à pourvoir au sein de notrecentre dentaire. Il s'agit d'une structure équipée des dernières technologiesqui vous permettra de prendre en charge votre patientèle dans les meilleuresconditions ! Une équipe administrative à l'écoute et des assistantes dentairespour vous accompagner lors de vos soins. Pour cette opportunité, nous proposonsune rémunération au pourcentage comprise entre 27% et 32%, selon votreexpérience.A propos du poste :Les avantages du centre dentaire Un laboratoire de prothèse dédié Des centres modernes et équipés des dernières technologies (ETK, A-Dec,Geistlich, 3Shape) Un parcours d'intégration spécifique pour les praticiens juniors : expertise,conseil et formation Des formations internes dispensées par des intervenants experts en adéquationavec l'évolution des techniques dentaires Un partage d'expériences entre confrères Un binôme avec des assistant(es) dentaires dédié(es) diplômé(es) Un personnel dédié à la présentation des devis, du suivi administratif et de lagestion optimisée du planning ; Une rémunération attractive entre 27% et 32% selon votre expérience et votrespécialitéComment s'y rendre Le centre se situe 53 rue Victor Hugo 94140 AlfotvillePostulez directement sur cette annonce ou contactez-nous à l'adresse et numérosuivant :dentiste a  ou au .Profil recherché :Profil recherché : Omnipraticien, Orthodontiste, Pédodontiste, Implantologue,Parodontiste, Endodondiste Qualités requises : capacité d'écoute, diplomatie etd'empathie envers le patient Type de contrat : Cadre salarié, CDI, temps pleinou partiel Niveau d'expérience : tous niveau Vous êtes dentiste issue d'uneformation dans l'union européenne, nous vous accompagnons dans vos démarchesafin d'exercer en France.

column20: Travel Nurse RN - ICU - Intensive Care Unit - $2,046 per week
column32:
TotalMed Staffing is seeking a travel nurse RN ICU - Intensive Care Unit for a travel nursing job in Rapid City, South Dakota.

Job Description & Requirements

  • Specialty: ICU - Intensive Care Unit
  • Discipline: RN
  • Start Date: 10/30/2023
  • Duration: 13 weeks
  • 36 hours per week
  • Shift: 12 hours, nights
  • Employment Type: Travel

    • We are seeking a Registered Nurse-Intensive Care Unit for a travel assignment in Rapid City South Dakota.

    Totalmed jobs Job ID #1277389. Pay package is based on 12 hour shifts and 36 hours per week (subject to confirmation) with tax-free stipend amount to be determined. Posted job title: Registered Nurse-Rapid City in South Dakota

    About TotalMed Staffing

    TotalMed is a Top Ten, travel nursing and healthcare staffing agency with the mission of igniting purpose in healthcare. The organization staffs nurses, therapists, pharmacists, and other clinicians of all specialties in all 50 states. They offer local and travel jobs and match caregivers with the right organization to assist both facilities and patients. As an organization, they focus on putting highly-skilled staff into facilities to ensure adequate staffing for a better patient experience.



    TotalMed specializes in recruiting and placing healthcare professionals in travel, PRN, and permanent positions across the country in Nursing and Allied Health. Throughout 2020, the organization filled roles at even the most short-staffed facilities during the most challenging time in healthcare. By matching the right travel healthcare professional with the right organization, TotalMed continues to offer a lifeline to facilities and their patients.

    Benefits

  • Weekly pay
  • Guaranteed Hours
  • Continuing Education
  • 401k retirement plan
  • Sick pay
  • Wellness and fitness programs
  • Referral bonus
  • Employee assistance programs
  • Medical benefits
  • Dental benefits
  • Vision benefits
  • Benefits start day 1

column32: A propos de l'entreprise :Dentego est une enseigne créée en 2013. Fruit de compétences et de valeurs partagées par ses fondateurs, Dentego a à coeur de promouvoir la santé bucco-dentaire accessible pour tous. Dentego garantit des traitements les plus adaptés aux besoins des patients, prodigués par le dentiste de leur choix qui les accompagne tout au long de leur traitement afin de leur proposer des soins dentaires au prix le plus juste.Gage de proximité et d'accessibilité, toutes les spécialités (orthodontie, pédodontie, implantologie ) sont réunies au sein d'un même centre. Le patient bénéficie ainsi d'une pluralité de soins dans un lieu unique. Pour parvenir à garantir la qualité des soins, la sécurité des patients et une expérience optimale, Dentego s'appuie sur une équipe aux compétences variées et complémentaires.A propos du poste :Les avantages des centres dentaires Dentego Un laboratoire de prothèse dédié Des centres modernes et équipés des dernières technologies (ETK, A-Dec, Geistlich, 3Shape) Un parcours d'intégration spécifique pour les praticiens juniors : expertise, conseil et formation Des formations internes dispensées par des intervenants experts en adéquation avec l'évolution des techniques dentaires Un partage d'expériences entre confrères Un binôme avec des assistant(es) dentaires dédié(es) diplômé(es) Un personnel dédié à la présentation des devis, du suivi administratif et de la gestion optimisée du planning ; Une rémunération attractive entre 27% et 32% selon votre expérience et votre spécialité Mutuelle d'entreprise et Contrat de prévoyance santé Partenariats bancaires, tarifs préférentiels Tickets RestaurantsDéroulement de l'entretien- Un échange téléphonique avec notre équipe recrutement- Une visite de centre avec le Responsable Régional- Un entretien clinique afin d'échanger avec un de nos dentistes référentsPostulez directement sur cette annonce ou contactez-nous à l'adresse et numéro suivant :dentiste a  ou Comment s'y rendre Le centre se situe au 2, Rue Docteur Burnet - 27200 VernonProfil recherché :Profil recherché Omnipraticien, Pédodontiste, Chirurgien oral Qualités requises : capacité d'écoute, diplomatie et d'empathie envers le patient Type de contrat : Cadre salarié, CDI, temps plein ou partiel Niveau d'expérience : tous niveaux d'expérienceChirurgien-Dentiste dans un état de l'Union Européenne Vous avez un niveau basique en Français (A2/B1), la Dentego Mobility vous accompagne dans la réalisation de votre projet professionnel en France. Nous vous proposons un accompagnement dédié et personnalisé pour :- Votre inscription à l'ordre des chirurgiens-dentistes- Votre recherche de logement- Vous propose des cours de Français avec un professeur agréé

column32:
SF Tooling Group ist eine in­ter­na­tio­nal auf­ge­stell­te Un­ter­neh­mens­grup­pe ­aus dem Werk­zeug- und For­men­bau mit Stand­ort in Deutsch­land, den USA und in Chi­na. Im Be­reich Alu­mi­ni­um­druck­guss­for­men und -werk­zeu­gen sind wir Welt­markt­füh­rer. Bei­ der Schaufler Tooling GmbH & Co. KG in Laichingen ent­wick­eln und fer­ti­gen 160 en­ga­gier­te Mit­ar­bei­ter Guss­for­men für an­spruchs­vol­le Druck­guss­tei­le ­für den Mo­to­ren-, Ge­trie­be- und Ka­ros­se­rie­bau. Un­se­re Kun­den sind er­folg­rei­che Au­to­mo­bil­her­stel­ler und de­ren Zu­lie­fer­er in der gan­zen Welt.

Für unseren Hauptstandort in Laichingen sind wir ab sofort auf der Suche nach einem engagierten

Personalsachbearbeiter – Entgeltabrechnung in Teilzeit (m/w/d)

Ihre Aufgaben:

  • Selbständige Vorbereitung, Durchführung und Nachbereitung der Lohn- und Gehaltsabrechnung einschließlich aller Melde- und Bescheinigungsverfahren
  • Ansprechpartner in allen abrechnungs-, steuer- und sozialversicherungsrechtlichen Fragestellungen
  • Administration von Eintritt bis Austritt eines Mitarbeiters (Arbeitsverträge und Arbeitszeugnisse erstellen; Bescheinigungen für die Mitarbeiter)
  • Pflege/Handling der Zeiterfassung

    • Ihr Profil:

  • Sie bringen bereits Erfahrung im Bereich der Entgeltabrechnung mit
  • Sie besitzen fundierte Kenntnisse im Sozialversicherungs- und Lohnsteuerrecht
  • Sie haben ein freundliches Auftreten
  • Ihr Arbeitsstil zeichnet sich durch strukturiertes und selbständiges Arbeiten aus

    • Wir bieten:

  • Eine zielgerichtete Einarbeitung in einem freundlichen und engagierten Team
  • Interessante und abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben
  • Vielfältige Entwicklungsmöglichkeit in einem international aufgestellten Unternehmen
  • flache Hierarchien
  • Betriebliche Altersvorsorge
  • Jobrad / E-Bike Leasing
  • Flexible Zeiteinteilung durch Gleitzeit und Arbeitszeitkonten
  • Fahrtkostenzuschuss
  • Mitarbeiter Events
  • fachbezogene Weiterbildungen

    • Das klingt spannend? Dann schicken Sie uns noch heute Ihre Bewerbung per Mail!

    Wir freuen uns auf Sie

    Schaufler Tooling GmbH & Co. KG

    Jana Söll

    Goethestraße 72

    Laichingen

    Tel.:

column20: Sr. Manager, Sr. Corporate Counsel (Product Safety)
column37: Get to know The Pokémon Company International
column39: The Pokémon Company International, a subsidiary of The Pokémon Company in Japan, manages the property outside of Asia and is responsible for brand management, licensing, marketing, the Pokémon Trading Card Game, the animated TV series, home entertainment, and the official Pokémon website. Pokémon was launched in Japan in 1996 and today is one of the most popular children's entertainment properties in the world.
column40: Learn more online at  and  And check out Twitter (), LinkedIn (émon), Youtube (), and Instagram ().
column43: Job Title: Sr. Manager, Legal Counsel
column46: Job Summary: Provides legal advice and counsel to the organization in support of business activities and transactions. Oversees the activities and work-products of attorneys and support staff.
column48: FLSA Classification (US Only): Exempt
column64: People Manager: Yes
column69: Serve as a Senior Manager, Senior Corporate Counsel on legal matters related to product safety on all Pokémon product lines and develop and update international and domestic product safety strategies and effective product safety programs for the company and subsidiaries.
column71: Manage and provide legal advice to the company and subsidiaries on all aspects of product safety issues and regulatory requirements globally.
column73: Develop policies, procedures, and training programs to support the company and subsidiaries in adhering to product safety and regulatory compliance requirements.
column76: Effectively establish global regulatory labeling and product safety testing programs, and other compliance guidelines and manuals from a regulatory perspective.
column79: Work on primary processes including vendor onboarding, safety analysis, design and labeling control, and recall action and establish best practices for the company and subsidiaries.
column82: Keep up-to-date on new legislation and regulations to ensure the company maintains the highest compliance standards. This includes working with the Production Team, our subsidiaries, and our business partners to ensure that legal interpretations are aligned.
column84: Develop and implement factory audit strategies and process and provide guidance on implementation.
column89: Membership in good standing with the Washington State Bar, or admission in a state with Washington State Bar reciprocity.
column92: Ten+ (10+) years of relevant legal professional experience, plus two (2) years of management experience or a demonstrated equivalent level of expertise.
column95: 5 years of demonstrated work experience in the area of product safety and product regulatory affairs (in-house or external). Prior in-house experience preferred.
column97: Strong knowledge of regulatory requirements such as CPSIA/ASTM, Prop 65 (USA), Toy Directive (EU), and ISO.
column100: Experience with children’s entertainment (preferred).
column103: Exceptional drafting, negotiation, communication (written and verbal), and interpersonal skill.
column105: Demonstrable experience innovating new processes to streamline operations and increase efficiency, transparency, and comprehension between client teams and legal.
column107: Experience working with multinational corporations and/or client and possessing a demonstrably strong ability to facilitate cross-cultural communications.
column111: Passion for Pokémon: Develops an understanding of the Pokémon brand, the impact it has on our people, culture, business, fans, and communities, and applying that knowledge and passion to everything you do.
column114: Challenging the Expected: Approaches challenges with curiosity and creativity, embracing the possibility of failure as an opportunity to learn something new, develop innovative ideas, solve complex problems and identify unique opportunities.
column117: Integrity and Respect: Demonstrates integrity and respect by leading with empathy, listening to others, seeking out different perspectives, and taking personal responsibility for decisions, actions, and results.
column120: Dedicated to Quality: Takes ownership to maintain and promote high standards, looks for new ways to learn and improve, and embraces a growth mindset to seek and apply feedback from others in an effort to continuously improve.
column122: Building Relationships: Develops and strengthens relationships, adopting a “team first” mentality and working collaboratively to solve problems and meet shared goals.
column125: Delighting Customers: Listens and understands the interests and needs of our customers and stakeholders, making them feel heard and important, and embracing these learnings to continue delivering a unique Pokémon experience.
column132: Company events that celebrate the spirit of Pokémon
column138: Base salary range: $170,000.00 - $254,000.00. This range is applicable for the labor market where the role is intended to be hired. For this role, new hires generally start between $170,000.00-$201,400.00. Final base salary is directly related to each candidates' qualifications and experience uniquely.
column146: Employer-paid long and short-term income protection insurance
column157: The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by people assigned to this role. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties, and skills required. Employees may be required to perform duties outside of their normal responsibilities from time to time, as needed. For roles in the United Kingdom, candidates will need the right to work. In some cases, and for some roles, the Company may be able to arrange a visa. For roles in Ireland, this role requires candidates to have the right to live and work in the Republic of Ireland. However, we welcome applications from all nationalities and may consider supporting an employment permit application, in appropriate and suitable cases

column35:
Provides direct service, care coordination and education to patients of Yakima Valley Farm Workers Clinic (YVFWC) for various programs. Provides information and support to internal and external partners.



Occasionally may need to work after hours and once in a while Saturdays. This candidate will be required to travel to most Oregon sites (mileage reimbursement available and shift differentials if needed).



This SCC position is unique. You will be providing classes to educate clients on proper asthma management. Classes will be in-person in class setting and online in English and Spanish.



What We Offer
column43: $19-$24/hour DOE with ability to go higher for highly experienced candidates.
column46: 100% employer-paid health insurance for employees including Medical, Dental, Vision, Rx, 24/7 telemedicine; profit sharing, 403(b) retirement plan, generous paid time off, paid holidays, and more.
column48: Executes incoming calls, assesses client/patient needs, and identifies appropriate services that are comprehensive and individualized to best serve each client/patient.
column64: Collects appropriate documentation to support and determine program services eligibility.
column69: Assists client/patient with scheduling dates for appointments or classes.
column71: Processes patient referrals for a variety of services including Medical, Dental, and programs including Behavioral Health.
column73: Monitors and documents active referrals and client participation.
column76: Assists patients with completion of applications and forms required by the program(s) they will participate in. Ensures patient information is complete and entered in appropriate data system.
column79: Responds to basic questions from patients.
column82: Provides follow-up contact with patient regarding service and referrals recommended. Encourages client participation and retention in various programs and classes.
column84: Performs work to align with productivity goals and standards including # patients, # encounters, # appointments scheduled and # classes facilitated.
column89: Provides program administrative support such as data entry, client file management, report development and contract compliance.
column92: Coordinates and promotes YVFWC programs. Recruits clients/patients for dental services, medical services, social services or education classes. Reserves conference rooms, obtains supplies, organizes snacks for classes.
column95: Presents program information in various internal and external community meetings and functions as requested.
column97: Education: High School Diploma or General Education Diploma (GED).
column100: Experience: One year of administrative support and customer service experience. Two years administrative support experience in a social services or healthcare setting preferred.
column103: Licenses/Certificates/Registration: Applicable license or certification. Some positions may require program specific certification. Valid Driver s License and proof of automobile liability insurance coverage.
column105: Knowledge/Skills/Abilities Required: Bilingual (English/Spanish) preferred. Must demonstrate the ability to communicate at level 9 on the language proficiency scale to receive bilingual differential pay. Ability to plan, coordinate and organize work projects. Ability to provide professional written and verbal presentations. Ability to prioritize work and handle a variety of tasks simultaneously, with frequent interruptions. Ability to effectively interact with the public, patients, and clinic staff in a professional manner. Ability to understand and apply program requirements and applicable local, state and federal guidance. Knowledge of the social and health agencies in the area and services they provide. Effective verbal, written and listening communication skills. Basic proficiency with a variety of computer programs including Microsoft Office, Word and Excel.
column106:
About YVFWC



We serve more than 197,000 patients across 28 medical clinics, 15 dental clinics, 11 pharmacies, and 49 program sites in two states. We are Level 3 Certified as a Patient-Centered Medical Home (PCMH). With integrated services including medical, dental, pharmacy, orthodontia, primary care nutritional counseling, autism screening, and primary care behavioral health, YVFWC s patient-centered model of care offers patients the full spectrum of care and shelter assistance, energy assistance, weatherization, HIV and AIDS counseling and testing, home visits, and four mobile medical/dental clinics.



Working at YVFWC



Working in our organization means being the passionate champion for those who have no voice. It means having the opportunity to work with underserved populations and with peers committed to the same work.



At Farm Workers Clinic

column35:
WHO WE ARE



Tech Etch primarily specializes in manufacturing precision-engineered components and flexible printed circuits in the Aerospace and Defense, Medical Devices, and Electronics and Telecommunications industries. Our mission is to inspire, create, and provide innovative solutions that enhance lives globally. We develop meaningful, long-term partnerships between our employee-owners and the industry leaders we serve. Our employees make up a united team of individuals who value positivity, teamwork, and growth with a mission to advance their skillsets and success.



ABOUT THE JOB



As the Manufacturing Engineer , you will support the part and process development of assigned parts from design to production, prepare part routers, troubleshoot problems in assigned processes, plan and execute the assigned Installation/Operation Qualifications, and support continuous improvement activities.
column43: Determine manufacturing processes for new parts, reducing cost and improving yield on existing parts
column46: Optimize processes by improving quality, efficiency, and safety, as well as reducing downtime
column48: Develop tooling, write instructions, and interface with customers regarding the ability to manufacture.
column64: Develop and control processes related to the manufacture of thin metal precision components, vent filters, conductive fabrics, board-level shields, and more.
column69: Identify, design, and integrate automated solutions through the use of new technologies and a dedication to innovation.
column71: A Bachelor's Degree in an engineering discipline or equivalent experience.
column73: Strong written and verbal communication skills
column76: Desire to work in a hands-on, fast-paced environment
column79: Good project management skills
column82: 3-5+ Years of process engineering and/or manufacturing engineering experience
column84: Technical aptitude and a passion for innovative solutions
column89: Competitive Pay with Bonus Potential
column92: Employee Stock Ownership
column95: 20 Vacation Days + 10 Holidays
column97: Low-Cost Medical, Dental, Vision, and Voluntary Life Insurance
column100: Flex Spending Accounts
column103: 401k with Company Match
column105: Wellness Incentive Program
column107: Employee Assistance Program
column111: Professional Development & Career Advancement Pathways
column114: Tuition Assistance Program
column117: Quarterly & Personal Performance Bonus Opportunities
column118:
HEAR FROM OUR TEAM:



Equal Opportunity Employer/Veterans/Disabled



Founded in 1964, Tech Etch operates facilities in Plymouth, MA, Fall River, MA, and Litchfield, MN



ISO 9001:2015 & AS9100D certified.



*NO OUTSIDE AGENCIES, PLEASE*



Accessibility: If you need an accommodation as part of the employment process please contact Human Resources

Equal Opportunity Employer, including disabled and veterans.

column32:
Position overview

Position title: Assistant Professor of Economics Salary range: A reasonable salary range estimate for this position is $99,100-$ 124,300.

The posted UC Academic salary scales set the minimum pay as determined by rank and/or step at appointment. See the following table(s) for the salary scale(s) for this position

The base salary range, from the salary table(s), for this position is $99,100-$ 124,300.

'Off-scale salaries' and other components of pay, i.e., a salary that is higher than the published system-wide salary at the designated rank and step, are offered when necessary to meet competitive conditions, qualifications, and experience.

Additional UCSD salary information can be found here:

Application Window

Open date: October 2, 2023

Next review date: Monday, Nov 13, 2023 at 11:59pm (Pacific Time)

Apply by this date to ensure full consideration by the committee.

Final date: Friday, May 31, 2024 at 11:59pm (Pacific Time)

Applications will continue to be accepted until this date, but those received after the review date will only be considered if the position has not yet been filled.

Position description

The School of Global Policy and Strategy (GPS) at UC San Diego invites applications for a tenure-track Assistant Professor in the fields of International Economics and closely related fields. The school seeks an outstanding scholar doing empirical research on issues related to the global economy, including trade and trade policy, multinational firms, international macroeconomics, exchange rates, and immigration. Faculty are expected to produce original research and publish in highly ranked academic journals, to teach courses at the undergraduate and graduate levels, to supervise and mentor graduate students, and to engage in select service activities

Qualifications

Basic qualifications (required at time of application)

At the time of application candidates must either have a Ph.D. (or equivalent degree) or be ABD (all but dissertation) in Economics or related field.

Research experience, teaching experience, and a commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion are highly desirable.

Additional qualifications (required at time of start)

Must hold a PhD in Economics or related field by start date of appointment.

Preferred qualifications

We are particularly interested in scholars with expertise on issues related to the global economy, including trade and trade policy, multinational firms, international macroeconomics, exchange rates, and immigration.

Application Requirements

Document requirements

  • Curriculum Vitae - Your most recently updated C.V.

  • Cover Letter

  • Statement of Research

  • Statement of Teaching

  • Statement of Contributions to Diversity - Applicants should summarize their past or potential contributions to diversity. See our Faculty Equity site for more information.

  • One Writing Sample

    • Apply link:

    Help contact:

    Campus Information

    The University of California, San Diego is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer advancing inclusive excellence. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, age, covered veteran status, or other protected categories covered by the UC nondiscrimination policy.

    As a University employee, you will be required to comply with all applicable University policies and/or collective bargaining agreements, as may be amended from time to time. Federal, state, or local government directives may impose additional requirements.

    The University of California prohibits smoking and tobacco use at all University controlled properties.

    The UC San Diego Annual Security & Fire Safety Report is available online at: This report provides crime and fire statistics, as well as institutional policy statement & procedures. Contact the UC San Diego Police Department at if you want to obtain paper copies of this report.

    Job location

    San Diego, California

column35:
The principle function of the Dental Hygienist is to provide preventative and expanded function periodontal treatment to patients.



What We Offer
column46: Maintains patient medical records, updating patient medical history and vital signs as needed.
column48: Conducts complete patient X-ray procedure including taking, developing and storing the X-Rays as necessary.
column64: Completes periodontal charting as directed.
column69: Prepares tools and equipment necessary for the Provider and assists Provider with the exams as necessary.
column71: Performs preventative periodontal care on patients including scaling, prophylaxis, root planing, and the application of preventative agents and sealants.
column73: Performs expanded functions including placing and carving amalgam and composite restorations, application of cavity liners, and placement/removal of temporary crowns.
column76: Administers local anesthesia and nitrous oxide analgesia as necessary.
column79: Provides education and counsel for patients in oral hygiene. Formulates dental hygiene treatment plans for patients, consulting the provider as needed.
column82: Participates in the clinic s infection control program, including sterilization of instruments and cleaning of operatories as needed. Provides input to the Dental Leadership team to assist in the development of goals and methods to increase efficiency of the Dental Clinic as needed.
column84: May participate in the development, implementation, and coordination of dental education programs provided inside and outside the organization.
column89: Performs clinical responsibilities in alignment with TJC, HRSA and org requirements.
column92: Performs clinical responsibilities in alignment with The Joint Commission (TJC), Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA), and YVFWC requirements.
column95: Education: Graduation from a Dental Hygiene school.
column97: Licenses/Certificates/Registration: Active WA Dental Hygiene certification within 90 days of employment.
column100: Knowledge/Skills/Abilities: Bilingual (English/Spanish) preferred. Must demonstrate the ability to communicate at level 10 on the language proficiency scale to receive bilingual differential pay. Knowledge of standard dental practices and current hygiene concepts. Knowledge of and skilled in the delivery of dental anesthetic. Knowledge of and skilled in placing restorations. Ability to effectively assess, adapt and interact with a variety of patients of all ages, and employees in a professional manner. Ability to effectively manage one s time, schedule, and resources to ensure that work is completed efficiently, appropriately, and within required timelines. High level of dexterity and coordination. Basic proficiency with a variety of computer programs including Electronic Dental Records, Microsoft Outlook, Word and Excel.
column102:
About YVFWC



We serve more than 197,000 patients across 28 medical clinics, 15 dental clinics, 11 pharmacies, and 49 program sites in two states. We are Level 3 Certified as a Patient-Centered Medical Home (PCMH). With integrated services including medical, dental, pharmacy, orthodontia, primary care nutritional counseling, autism screening, and primary care behavioral health, YVFWC s patient-centered model of care offers patients the full spectrum of care and shelter assistance, energy assistance, weatherization, HIV and AIDS counseling and testing, home visits, and four mobile medical/dental clinics.



Working at YVFWC



Working in our organization means being the passionate champion for those who have no voice. It means having the opportunity to work with underserved populations and with peers committed to the same work.



At Farm Workers Clinic
column103: We will consistently trust one another to work for the common good. We will foster integrity by demonstrating ethical behavior and insisting on doing what we say we will do.
column105: We will demonstrate transparency by being candid and truthful no matter the risk.
column107: We will create partnerships to strengthen ourselves and our community.
column111: We will fight for just treatment for all individuals.
column114: We will let joy in.
column117: We have the courage to be an agent of change and refuse anything short of excellence.
column118: Our mission celebrates diversity. We are committed to equal opportunity employment.

Medical Technologist Job inRome, Georgia



Are you a skilled and passionate Medical Technologist looking for a fulfilling career opportunity in the heart of Rome, Georgia? We have an exciting position waiting for you!
column43: 13 weeks contract
column46: Perform a variety of plex laboratory tests and procedures.
column48: Analyze and report accurate and timely test results.
column64: Maintain laboratory equipment and ensure quality control.
column69: Collaborate with healthcare professionals to provide critical diagnostic information.
column71: Bachelor's degree in Medical Technology or related field.
column73: ASCP or equivalent certification preferred.
column76: Strong attention to detail and analytical skills.
column79: Excellent munication and teamwork abilities.

column35:
Full-Time, Part-Time, or PRN Occupational Therapist (OT) position available at Willcare in Lake Katrine, NY!

At LHC Group, we embrace a culture of caring, belonging, and trust and enjoy the meaningful connections that come from it: for the whole patient, their families, each other, and the communities we serve it truly is all about helping people. You can find a home for your career here.

As a full-time Occupational Therapist , you can expect:
column43: The ability to build in-person trusted therapist-patient relationships
column46: Continuing education and tuition reimbursement opportunities
column48: Independence and autonomy
column64: Career growth possibilities
column67: Give your passion to serve others and your drive for better, more advanced quality healthcare.

Are you looking for a new therapist job? Would you like to spend the season somewhere you've never been? Hospitals, Clinics, Outpatient, Schools and Rehab Facilities nationwide are looking for qualified Speech Language Pathologist for their short term locum travel assignments. With the HCEN Network of staffing agencies, therapist like you receive competitive job offers from the nation's top healthcare employers every day!

The HealthCare Employment Network works with agencies and facilities nationwide offering:

column34:
Controls Engineer

Waverly, OH

Responsibilities

Generates Floor Plans, Process Flow Diagrams, Ladder Logic in the installation and programming of PLCs.

Follows the entire build of Robotics, or Special Purpose Equipment and Fixtures from Purchase Order to PPAP and into Production.

Provides engineering support to other departments within the Company as directed by the Engineering Manager.

Prepares work schedules with interim end target estimates for all projects within his/her responsibility.

Supports APQP Team and Program Managers with the creation of technical specifications for the purchase of automation, robotics, assembly equipment and automated check fixtures.

Searches out and implements new technologies and Continuous Improvement opportunities in the machining and assembly fields.

Initiate plans and ideas for cost reductions and/or quality improvement measures.

Maintain proper filing system to ensure all information is properly stored and easily retrieved.

Follows and enforces the guidelines and rules as defined in the Employee Handbook and Company policies.

Carries out assigned responsibilities under TS16949 and ISO 14001.

Any other reasonable request made by management.

Contributes to a safe, clean and comfortable work environment that complements the Occupational Health and Safety Act by ensuring the principles of the 5S discipline (simplify, separate, sanitize, standardize and support) are supported and adhered to.

Ensures he/she is in full compliance with applicable federal, state, and local laws, while representing Kirchhoff Automotive or during the use of any provided equipment.

Arranges technical training for maintenance technicians.

Qualifications

Work Experience (provide details and minimum # of years required)

3 years post secondary school education, preferably in Electrical, Industrial or related on the job experience with specific discipline in controls and robotics.

Skills (language, technical, computer etc.)

Skills What skills are required to perform the work?

Demonstrated ability to multi-task

Organized and self-motivated professional

Must be able to communicate fluently in both written and spoken English

Must be able to relate / communicate well with people at all levels

Blueprint Reading, Basic Measuring Techniques, Proficient with CAD (preferably AUTOCAD or E-PLAN) \

Knowledge What knowledge of methods, procedures, equipment/technology are required?

Knowledge of ANSI, SAE and other industry/customer related standards

Knowledge of GD&T, QFD, Design for Manufacturing, VE/VA, DOE, FMEA, DFMEA/PFMEA, Reliability Engineering Plans

Must be very familiar with Automotive Manufacturing Process, Synchronous Manufacturing, SPC, 8Ds, Control Plans, Continuous Improvement Techniques

Working knowledge of TS16949 and ISO14001

Knowledge of presses, machining equipment, material handling equipment, inspection/gauging equipment, tool room equipment, metal finish equipment .

Judgment Exercises judgment:

Selecting vendors for quotations

Determining all relevant details for quotation summary

Prioritizing activities and recognizing critical tasks

Accountability Is accountable in areas of:

Successful implementation of equipment

Ensuring equipment meets quality, productivity, reliability and cost requirements

Accuracy and completeness of recommendation summary

Meeting program timing requirements pertaining to equipment

Contacts Establishes/maintains relationships:

Employees within Production Control, Quality Assurance, Production, Purchasing, Sales, Accounting, Maintenance and team members

Outside vendors

Education

Bachelors Degree in Electrical Engineering or 3 years post secondary school education, preferably in Electrical, Industrial or related on the job experience with specific discipline in controls and robotics.



PandoLogic. Keywords: Control Systems Engineer, Location: Waverly, OH - 45690

column20: Experienced Mercedes Benz Mechanic needed in NYC
column35:
Job Description Experienced Mercedes Benz Mechanic needed in NYC!



Are you an experienced Automotive Technician with a passion for Mercedes Benz vehicles? Looking for skilled and passionate mechanics for a Manhattan/New York City dealership! Located on a 330,000 square foot lot on 11th Avenue between 53rd and 54th Streets, Mercedes-Benz Manhattan is the ONLY MERCEDES-BENZ DEALERSHIP IN THE COUNTRY OWNED AND OPERATED BY MERCEDES-BENZ .



QUALIFICATIONS:
column43: Minimum of 3 years of Mercedes dealership experience
column46: Master certification through the Standards of Excellence Program
column48: A.S.E. Certification (strongly recommended)
column64: Outstanding preparation, attitude, and teamwork
column69: Ability to commute into and out of Manhattan.
column71: Perform diagnosis and advanced electrical repairs on Mercedes Benz vehicles.
column73: Collaborate with Team Leader to complete in-house training.
column76: Fulfill all training requirements set forth by MBUSA and MBM
column79: Competitive salary ranging from $30 to $70 per hour. (earn up to $150,000 based on experience)
column82: Industry-leading benefits package including: Healthcare, dental, vision, PTO, tuition reimbursement and much more!
column84: Possible sign-on bonus for eligible candidates
column89: Flexible work schedule (first or second shift - but dealership closes at 7pm and is closed Sundays)
column92: Multiple retirement packages with a generous 401k match. Commuter bonus up to $500 a month. Tuition reimbursement. Employee car lease program. Gym reimbursement and more!
column93:
Apply now and enjoy a rewarding career with excellent earning potential, top-notch benefits, and the opportunity to work with the iconic Mercedes Benz brand. If you meet the above qualifications and would like to apply for this position, please click APPLY NOW and upload your most current resume or you may email your resume to our recruiter, Barry Tacktill at

Questions regarding this position can be addressed by emailing or calling .Thank you in advance for applying, however, only qualified candidates will be contacted



Pay Details: $30.00 to $70.00 PER HOUR



Equal Opportunity Employer/Veterans/Disabled



To read our Candidate Privacy Information Statement, which explains how we will use your information, please navigate to



The Company will consider qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records subject to federal contractor requirements and/or security clearance requirements.

column20: Travel Nurse RN - Telemetry - $2,326 per week
column32:
LeaderStat is seeking a travel nurse RN Telemetry for a travel nursing job in Pueblo, Colorado.

Job Description & Requirements

  • Specialty: Telemetry
  • Discipline: RN
  • Start Date: ASAP
  • Duration: 13 weeks
  • 36 hours per week
  • Shift: 12 hours
  • Employment Type: Travel

    • Nurse (RN) Telemetry | Nurse (RN) in Pueblo, CO



    LeaderStat is currently seeking a Nurse (RN) with Telemetry | Nurse (RN) experience for a(n) 13 week contract in CO.



    Start Date: 10/3/2023

    End Date: 1/2/2024

    Shift: Night Shift (7p-7a)



  • 1 year of experience working as a full-time Registered Nurse
  • Clinical experience within the last 2 years
  • Current State Licensure
  • Current Relevant Certifications (BLS, ACLS, etc)


    • The LeaderStat Difference

    Our LeaderStat recruiters are experts in Travel Nursing! We work hard to find the best travel nurse jobs for each candidate. However, our service doesn’t end at placement. We set you up for success by providing support throughout your contract… from start to finish!



    Our goal is to find the best travel nurse assignments to fit your individual needs. While you focus on providing top-notch care to your patients, we’ll handle the rest.



    LeaderStat Perks & Benefits

    As a Traveling Nurse with LeaderStat you receive excellent benefits:

  • Weekly Pay & Direct Deposit
  • W2 Employee Status
  • 401(k) Retirement Plan
  • Medical, Dental and Vision Insurance
  • Referral Bonuses
  • Dedicated Support Team


    • To learn more about LeaderStat visit

    #AcuteTravelers





    Estimated Pay Package



    Total Gross Pay Weekly $: 2518.60

    Pay Rate per Hour $: 32.30

    Weekly Housing Stipend $: 749.00

    Meals Allowance ($): 413.00



    *The above pay package is an estimate, please contact our team to put together your personalized pay package, as a variety of factors can influence your total pay.*

    LeaderStat Job ID #149633. Pay package is based on 12 hour shifts and 36 hours per week (subject to confirmation) with tax-free stipend amount to be determined. Posted job title: Telemetry - Registered Nurse

    About LeaderStat

    LeaderStat is a National staffing, recruiting, and consulting firm dedicated to the healthcare industry.

     

    For 20 years, LeaderStat has been dedicated to partnering with exceptional healthcare providers to find them the very best assignments throughout the country. Specializing in Travel Nursing, Interim Leadership, Executive Search, and Consulting. When you work with the LeaderStat team, you work with a recruiter who is dedicated to finding you the perfect assignment. Why would you settle for less?﻿

column32: Job DescriptionNine Films and TelevisionNine produces leading local shows including McLeod's Daughters, The Block, Married at First Sight and Underbelly. Such shows are commercialised as NFTV products eg. through merchandising, licencing and distribution deals. Our finance team is responsible for the reporting of Nine produced programs distributed locally and internationally. This involves financial reporting on a monthly basis (reconciliations, forecasting, budgeting and cashflow) and day to day management of revenue and expenses (e.g. royalty reporting, invoicing and payment of producer shares).Reporting to the Finance Manager, you will be responsible for day-to-day activities to ensure financial management of various NFTV Programs and Departments. This includes assisting with Month end reporting, Budgets & forecasting, and Cashflow reporting. Monthly review of departmental revenue and expenses and analysis of variances to budget and forecastMonthly revenue and expenditure full year forecasts and explanation of variances to budget, and forecast.Preparation of balance sheet reconciliations Preparation and presentation of monthly and full year forecast results to key users of financial information Monthly cashflow reporting Preparation of annual departmental budgets including Revenue and distribution expenses.Preparation of year end reporting and meeting audit requirementsDay-to day management of revenue and expenditure including invoicing and processing royalty paymentsPreparation of royalty distribution statements for producer shares and processing invoices.Preparation of quarterly ABS surveysPreparation of ad-hoc analysis and reporting as requested by internal stakeholders.Participates in and supports a team environmentQualificationsQualified Accountant (CA or CPA)Proven financial experienceStrong Excel, reconciliation skills, analytical skills and attention to detailAbility to work to a deadline and the ability to prioritise and manage their time and time of othersAbility to communicate in a clear, timely and consistent mannerA personal high standard of quality to their workAdditional InformationOur Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion:At Nine, we are committed to fostering a workforce that embraces all aspects of diversity and inclusion and where practices are equitable to ensure our people experience a sense of belonging. From day one, you'll be encouraged to bring your whole self to work and will be supported to perform at your best. Should you require any adjustments to the recruitment process in order to equitably participate, we encourage you to advise us at the time of encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, and of all ages, nationalities, backgrounds and cultures.

column35:
Children's Activities Associate at Kids Quest - TREASURE ISLAND RESORT & CASINO

Kids Quest Company Description:

Kids Quest is the largest hourly childcare provider and entertainment facility, offering play, games, and birthday parties at our partner resorts.

Our team is looking for a Children's Activities Associate to help join and lead our team!

Benefits and Perks of a Children's Activities Associate:
column43: Get Paid to Play - Earn tips on top of your hourly wage rate!
column46: Paid Trainings - Learn and gain leadership skills that you can use inside and outside of work!
column48: Health & Wellness Benefits - taking care of you and your family! For full time employees we offer health, vision and dental care plans. For all employees we have fun wellness programs like walking competitions with prizes, free employee assistance programs for overall wellness
column64: Plan for Your Future - we offer 401(k) for all employees including 401(k) company matching
column69: Discounts on Personal Child Care - receive half (50%) off the hourly child care rate for children between the ages of 30 months to 12 years of age! Have your kids play while you work and have fun!
column71: Quarterly Incentive Team Challenges - by being a part of our management team, you can help create fun team challenges to incentivize center growth and productivity.
column73: Monthly Team Rallies - Bring your pep and your cheer! Each month we celebrate our successes as a team and create new goals to help grow the business!
column76: Career Advancement Opportunities - we love to promote from within! We have a robust training program that will help you excel to the next level within our company! We strive to ensure our people have first opportunities when new center openings or positions are made available company-wide!
column79: Free Slushies and Half Off Food - Getting thirsty on job! No problem! Enjoy free slushies and free fountain drinks while working! Also, if you forget your lunch, help yourself to any of our food items for half (50%) off!!
column81: Job Summary of a Children s Activities Associate :
column82: You are a genuine, caring and responsible individual who can enthusiastically play and engage with children between the ages of 6 weeks through 12 years old. You have the skills to supervise our young guests responsibly and respectfully by bringing energy, excitement and fun to their lives while entrusted to our care.
column83: Qualification and Must-Have Skills of a Children s Activities Associate:
column84: Be passionate about play and children, enjoy meeting new people
column89: Must be able to complete and pass required background screening (which may include a drug test)
column92: Ability to work a variety of shifts, this includes evenings, weekends, and holidays
column95: A high school diploma, G.E.D. or equivalent (required)
column97: Experience in child care, day care, nannying, babysitting, and even coaching children s sports is a plus!
column100: Military veterans or reservists are encouraged to apply!
column103: Must be 18 years of age or older and can work in a casino/gaming environment
column105: Ability to handle changing priorities and use good judgment in stressful situations
column107: Basic computer proficiency and cash handling experience (preferred)
column109: Children s Activities Associate Core Job Duties:
column111: Report to your center management team while on duty.
column114: Come to work each day on-time, motivated and with a positive attitude.
column117: Understand and follow cash control processes and procedures.
column120: Maintain the Kids Quest dress code standards while on duty.
column122: Attend all scheduled meetings, workshops and required training programs
column125: Abide by all Kids Quest policies
column129: Embrace a fast-paced work and high-traffic play environment.
column134:
Apply now! Don't let this opportunity to have a fun, rewarding job pass you by!

Benefits:
column149:
• Weekend availability

    • COVID-19 considerations:

    All employees must pass a wellness screening prior to reporting to work. Masks are not required but optional upon employee discretion.

    Ability to commute/relocate:

  • Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)

    • Application Question(s):

  • Are you available to work week days until 11pm and weekends as late as 1am? Please let us know your availability.

    • Education:

  • High school or equivalent (Required)

    • Experience:

  • Childcare: 1 year (Preferred)

    • Work Location: In person

    #TREASUREKQ

column35:
EMERGENCY TECHNICIAN JOB SUMMARY:



Under close/general supervision by licensed personnel the Emergency Department (ED) Technician/Emergency Medical Technician (EMT) will perform a variety of functions in support and care of patients requiring urgent or emergency care in the Rapid Care or emergency medical setting.



REQUIREMENTS:



High School diploma or equivalent.



Proof of Emergency Medical Technician (EMT) certification from an approved institution program or CA Paramedic License.
column43: CA EMT License required.
column44:
Phlebotomy Certified Preferred but not required. Paramedic licensed allows phlebotomy in their scope of practice.



Current BLS Card certification from the American Heart Association.



Training and experience: Unless otherwise indicated, one year of current experience within the last three years in a comparable job classification required.



Maintenance of current Basic Life Support for HealthCare Workers.



Educated on and compliant with HIPAA regulations; maintains strict confidentiality of client information.



Complies with Infection Control, Standard Precautions and OSHA standards for the healthcare professional.



Able to wear personal protective equipment (e.g., face mask, goggles, latex/non-latex gloves) as needed.



Ability to work effectively within role independently and with other team members.



Ability to organize and complete work in a timely manner.



Ability to read, write and effectively communicate in English.



Ability to understand medical/surgical terminology.



Computer literacy including Microsoft Office Suite. Accurate and timely keyboarding skills, including word processing and data entry.



Proven ability to organize time and tasks.



Proven ability to work within multiple departments, receiving direction from multiple sources.



Proven ability to establish and maintain good working relationships.



PAY / BENEFITS

Estimated pay: $20.00 to $25.00 per hour based on qualifications (including but not limited to experience, education, certifications, and licensure where applicable).



Benefits may include medical, dental, vision, basic life and AD&D, optional supplemental life (employee, spouse, and/or child coverage), flexible spending accounts (medical and dependent care), 403b retirement with dollar for dollar match up to 5%, paid time off, and more available depending on employment status.



M/F/D/V/SO



EOE

column32:
Corporate Finance Partner - West Midlands



Excellent Package & Remote/Hybrid work options



Clark Wood have recently been instructed by highly reputable West midlands based accoutnancy business, to source an experienced Corporate Finance Director or Partner.



They key focuses of the role would be concentrating upon M&A work, transactions, funding, forecasting, with some additional exposure to lead advisory work and due diligence.



Clients would be mid market OMBs and SMEs, so an overall advisory mindset and skillset would be required. Deals in the region of £5mil to £200 mil.



As Corporate Finance Director or Partner you will bridge the gap between the Executives and the Senior Management team, by not only delivering the more complex reporting, but working with the more junior team members to provide guidance and support.



You will be able to lead meetings and relationships with your clients, providing detailed guidance on the information delivered and guide them through the transaction.



Acting as a lead on assignments, you will be able to pull all aspects together through strong leadership and technical ability. You will be encouraged to network with wider Corporate Finance teams within the business to ensure you are working on a National level to service clients and keep technical expertise current.



For further information on this role please contact Rich Kinsey at Clark Wood - /



#CW0823 %962269% %%finance%%

column32: Qui sommes-nous ?Euro-Information, filiale technologique de Crédit Mutuel Alliance Fédérale, conçoit, réalise, maintient et exploite un système dinformation commun utilisé par le  activités de développement et de production informatique au niveau national et international sont assurées par environ 4000 salariés répartis sur plusieurs sites géographiques au niveau national : Strasbourg, Nancy, Dijon, Orléans, Lyon, Lille, Cergy, Val de Fontenay, Paris et Nantes.Première Banque à adopter le statut dentreprise à mission, le Crédit Mutuel Alliance Fédérale sinvestit et sengage dans différentes missions sociales et environnementales :Laccompagnement de tous par notre organisation coopérative et mutualiste reste au cœur de notre  technologie au service de lhumain est une référence dans notre monde connecté.La solidarité et léco-responsabilité deviennent des axes clés dans notre développement.Notre raison dêtre : Ensemble, Ecouter et Agir. Pourquoi nous recrutons ? Vos missionsVous êtes en recherche demploi et vous souhaitez réorienter votre carrière vers une filière porteuse ? Euro-Information filiale technologique de Crédit Mutuel Alliance Fédérale vous propose de vous former au métier de Gestionnaire dApplication / Analyste dExploitation !Vous aurez pour mission principale la mise en place et la maintenance de lordonnancement et de lautomatisation des traitements informatiques conçus par nos équipes de développement.Pour ce faire, vous devrez acquérir :une connaissance technique des outils utilisés (ordonnanceur TWS, langage JCL) et des process spécifiques aux métiers de la production informatiqueune connaissance fonctionnelle des domaines applicatifs qui vous seront confiés (assurances, téléphonie mobile, prêts, comptabilité)Grâce à ces connaissances, vous aurez également un rôle dexpertise vis-à-vis des équipes de développement ainsi que des équipes assurant le monitoring 24/24 de notre production informatique. Ce que vous allez vivre chez nousTélétravail (2 jours par semaine)Rémunération fixe versée sur 13 moisRTTIntéressement, participation et abondementPlan épargne entreprise et PERCOContrat de santé collectifPrévoyanceRetraite supplémentaire prise en charge à 100% par lemployeurConditions bancaires et assurances préférentiellesPolitique parentale avantageuse Ce que nous allons aimer chez vousPour mener à bien vos missions, vous devrez travailler méthodiquement en faisant preuve dautonomie et de rigueur. Afin dassurer une bonne qualité de service nous attendrons de vous des qualités relationnelles et rédactionnelles.Comment intégrer nos équipes ?Disposer au minimum dun BAC +2 dans un domaine scientifique (mathématiques, biologie, chimie) ou dingénierie spécialiste/généraliste.Avoir de bonnes bases en AnglaisPrésenter de réelles motivations pour le domaine informatiqueEtre prêt(e) à sinvestir dans une formation technique et être disponible sur du long termeEtre en situation de demandeur d'emploiNous vous proposons dintégrer une formation technique de 2 mois, au cours de laquelle vous découvrirez, entre autres, les environnements JCL et TWS. Vous aurez loccasion de vous exercer lors de travaux pratiques tout en étant accompagné(e) par des intervenants dotés dune réelle expertise méès validation de cette formation, une embauche en CDI est possible sur les sites de Strasbourg, Lille (Verlinghem), Nantes, Lyon (Tassin la Demi-Lune) ou Fontenay sous Bois.
